  "detailed_description": "~ you are mountain - you are god ~<br><br>Ambient procedural mountain game, as seen on The Internet.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">FEATURES </h2>- no controls<br>- automatic save<br>- audio on/off switch<br>- time moves forward<br>- things grow and things die<br>- nature expresses itself<br><br>&quot;Welcome to an existential nightmare.&quot;<br>- Patrick Klepek, Giant Bomb<br><br>&quot;The time I spend with Mountain feels slightly more real to me than anything else inside my computer.&quot;<br>- Leigh Alexander, Gamasutra<br><br>&quot;\u201cMountain\u201d upends expectations, refusing to fit into preexisting categories.&quot;<br>- Justin Cone, Motionographer<br><br>&quot;I don\u2019t like to talk emotions but this game genuinely is so uplifting.&quot;<br>- Alice O'Connor, Rock Paper Shotgun<br><br>&quot;The only experience that has ever made me feel sad about a geological phenomenon.&quot;<br>- Andrew Webster, The Verge",
